channel.description:
This tutorial will show you how to add a level requirement to any command

Difficulty: 1/10

1)
Take the command you wish to use. For this tutorial I am using a simple spawn command.

[code]
        else if(cmd[0].equals("anal") ) {
Engine.playerItems.addItem(p, 1050, 1);
p.frames.sendMessage(p, "You just spawned a santa");
}
[/code]We all know in a condition, you can use && to add another part to the condition, which will make sure the command will not be executed unless both requirements are met..

2) for step 2, we add the level requirement.


[code]
        else if(cmd[0].equals("anal") && p.skillLvl[0] >= 50) {  /*The skill id can be changed to what you need it to be, for this example it is 0, and the level required for the command is 50.*/
Engine.playerItems.addItem(p, 1050, 1);
p.frames.sendMessage(p, "You just spawned a santa");
}
[/code]3) {Optional}.
If you want the game to return an error to the player if they do not have the required level, do this step instead of 2.
[code]
        else if(cmd[0].equals("anal") ) {
if (p.skillLvl[0] >= 50){
Engine.playerItems.addItem(p, 1050, 1);
p.frames.sendMessage(p, "You just spawned a santa");
}
else {
p.frames.sendMessage(p, "You need at least 50 in "chosen skill" to do that.");
}
}

[/code]
Hope this helps some people :D enjoy
